body:
@anuraaga I think we are on the same page and most things came out during the initial work as we had tests for them.

the spring-security thing is something that might be worth doing in general as it was something we documented, but didn't actively support. The integration appears to be wrapping a servlet request handler. I haven't pushed as hard on that one as yeah we didn't actually support it in the past.

To put another way, each thing we support in zipkin adds liability when moving to spring 3, 4 or whatever's next. I also don't want to support more things and to that degree I'm ok apologizing about the spring-security hook thing if that ends up not ever implemented by armeria.
